questions.sparql:
select DISTINCT ?frequent_flyer_program where { ?airlines	<type>	<Airline>. ?airlines	<airlines>	?frequent_flyer_program. } ORDER BY DESC(COUNT(?airlines))
OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1

select DISTINCT ?cities where { ?cities	<type>	<City>. ?inhabitants	<city>	?cities. ?cities	<country>	<Germany>. } GROUP BY ?cities
HAVING (COUNT(?inhabitants) > 250000) LIMIT 100

select DISTINCT ?countries where { ?countries	<type>	<Country>. ?volcanoes	<type>	<Volcano>. ?volcanoes	<locatedInArea>	?countries. } GROUP BY ?countries
HAVING (COUNT(?volcanoes) > ten) LIMIT 100

select COUNT(DISTINCT ?or_towns) where { ?or_towns	<inhabitants>	?inhabitants. } GROUP BY ?or_towns
HAVING (COUNT(?inhabitants) > 300000) LIMIT 100

select DISTINCT ?countries where { ?countries	<type>	<Country>. ?mountains	<type>	<Mountain>. ?mountains	<locatedInArea>	?countries. } GROUP BY ?countries
HAVING (COUNT(?mountains) > 100) LIMIT 100

select DISTINCT ?Who where { ?books	<type>	<Book>. ?books	<author>	?Who. } ORDER BY DESC(COUNT(?books))
OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1
